"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-05-24-Paris-2024-organizers-unveil-design-of-podiums-1tRYUyFs6qI-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CGTN  Copied  The podiums of the Paris Olympic and Paralympic Games were unveiled at the headquarters of the games' organizing committee on Thursday.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like the medals, the design of the podiums also draws its inspiration from the Eiffel Tower, with the metal lace structure outlining the exterior surface of the podium.\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featuring a sleek and elegant color scheme of grey and white, the podiums are made of wood and 100 percent recycled plastic, and employ a modular design to accommodate the needs of different events.\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 724, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, the shortest podium, used for individual events, consists of three modules and is approximately four meters long.\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The podium for the football award ceremony uses the most modules, totaling 43, with an overall length of 40 meters.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024's tweet on May 23 about the Olympic and Paralympic podiums.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999770353, \"rank\": 2.298625313679612e-11, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/@Paris2024  Each podium weighs approximately 45 kilograms.\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Organizing Committee has prepared a total of 685 modules, 45 of which are reserved as backup modules.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999479314, \"rank\": 5.20390745276679e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The podium is the ultimate symbol of performance and its celebration.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Olympic and Paralympic athletes, reaching the podium is an achievement.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the conclusion of a long journey,\\\" said Tony Estanguet, the president of the organizing committee.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1408, \"end\": 1422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medalists will stand on a 35-centimeter high podium, while silver and bronze medalists will stand on a 20cm high podium.\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The same design will be used for the Paralympics, but the top three athletes will all stand on a 20cm high podium with a sloped ramp on the side for wheelchair accessibility.\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u0